Boil a #kettle{} half-full.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Put the @Couscous{120%grams} into a #bowl{}.
Pour in the boiling @Water for the Couscous{200%ml} and stir in half the @Beef Stock Paste{20%grams}.
Cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side, ~{10%minutes}.
Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Honey{1%tbsp}, @Butter{20%grams} and the remaining beef stock to the pork.
Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{}. Share between your #bowls{}.
Top with the chipotle pork.
Crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}.
Enjoy!